  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">NIHR Global Health Research Unit on Health in Situations of Fragility</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">1) to develop a systematic program of research identifying effective strategies to enhance the quality, accountability, coverage, and accessibility of priority health interventions through an integrated &#x2018;systems for health&#x2019; approach to the growing burden of noncommunicable diseases (NCDs) and mental health. 2) to deploy cutting-edge methodologies for participatory health systems analysis and appraisal of community dynamics and resources to ensure that strategies to support intervention effectiveness are identified through rigorous analytical assessment. 3) to support development of a generalisable framework for fragility assessment as well as focused evidence regarding strategies to mitigate fragility for specific health interventions in localised settings.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">A UK and low- and middle-income country (LMIC) partnership that aims to analyse the challenges of delivering health services and promoting health in fragile situations, with the aim of identifying sources of resilience within formal health systems and local community mechanisms to facilitate effective provision for health priorities - particularly mental health and non-communicable disease - in situations of fragility.</narrative>
  </description>
